						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟavarman</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tribhº ••••• (Kulaśēkhara I): Year 39, Āṉi = 1306-07 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is much damaged. It refers to the king as ‘who was pleased to take every country’.</p>						

						<p>It appears to record a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> to provide for festivals and processions to the god Tirumuttīśvaram-uḍaiya-ṉāyaṉār of Kaḍuvaṉkuḍi in Mudiyakkuḍi-nāḍu in [••• ••• ••••], probably by the <hi rend="italic">ūravar</hi> of Mēlaik-Kaḍuvaṉkuḍi and Kīḻaik-Kaḍuvaṉkuḍi.</p>						

						<p>The signatory was Ōmandaṉ Iḷamaitaṭṭāṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
